column5: HIT BRONTE LAST NITE FOR A FEW HOURS LAST NITE IN THE PARK, ALL I CAN SAY IS CARCASSAES EVERYWHER, PRETTY DAMN DISCUSTING OH WELL IT NEVER CHANGES THERE YEAR AFTER YEAR ANYWAY, AS SOON AS YOU GET IN THE PARKING LOT ALL YOU CAN SMELL IS ROTTING FISH, THE CREEK IS UP AND MUDDY A FEW FISH MOVING THROUGH, DIDN'T GET ANY, SEEN A FEW PEOPLE CHASE SOME IN THE RAPIDS THATS NOTHING NEW TO SEE, AT LEAST THE FISH CAN GET UP AND HARD FOR SNAGGERS TO GET THEM CHEERS
That sounds about right. When the rainbows come in I wonder if they make it out of the first pool

Havent been up the creek for 3yrs, its disgusting.Igoto lowville instead, no tires,shopping carts or bags in the creek.I wonder if any runoff is coming from the auto wreckers yard. That might explain why so many die before passing that area.I saw a female salmon struggling at the tracks and not ready to lay her eggs.I wonder why?cheers
We stopped by Petro Park to see who was there last night.  There was a hen on the ground with a stick in its mouth, and all her roe spread over the grass.  It was very sad.  People make me upset...
preferably i like fishin there nov through dec and maybe before it closes, if it doesn't freeze less people more spots to cover.
went there today nothin much other than a few near black salmon...dirty high water...by the tim hortons there was none either.when do the rainbows come in and can u fish for them under the bridge?
you might want to check the regs lowville closed on sept 25th
407 to rebbeca st is the extended season, hwy2 to lake ontario is year round
